<subSubSection pageNumber="382" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="382">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="382">Note:</emphasis>
Although 
<normalizedToken originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
&amp; Eshbaugh (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="382">Baileya</emphasis>
19: 98. 1974) discussed the type material, as has been pointed out by Janser. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="382">Spices, Condiments Med. Pl. Ethiopia</emphasis>
: 38. 1981), there is confusion as to which sheet was intended as type - the authors say that a Clifford sheet is the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but also that it is on the IDC microfiche (i.e. = sheet 249.1 LINN). Janser. rejected both specimens in favour of a van Royen sheet in L. However, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="D’Arcy’s">D'Arcy's</normalizedToken>
later 1974 type statement is unequivocal, and has priority.
</paragraph>
